23 SECTION 1. DO NOT CODIFY. Legislative findings and intent.
24 (a) The General Assembly finds that the Secretary of the Department of
25 Corrections may add a surcharge to all inmate calls to offset the cost of
26 equipment and operations for security needs associated with inmate
27 communications.
28 (b) The General Assembly intends:
29 (1) The department to assess a surcharge on inmate calls to be
30 used to pay for certain expenses to offset the cost of security needs
31 associated with inmate communications; and
32 (2) To authorize a county sheriff in charge of a county jail to
33 assess a surcharge on inmate calls to offset the cost of security needs
34 associated with inmate communications.
